Product information

Description

With the Samsung OLED 4K 55S95D, you can watch vibrant, colorful images thanks to the QD-OLED screen. This TV dims and lights up individual pixels, or switches them off. Black is really black. Thanks to the Quantum Dots, the colors are always vibrant. So you see a clear difference between the sun on the street and surrounding shadows. Thanks to the OLED Glare Free coating, you're not bothered by reflections on your screen. Even when bright sunlight shines on the image, everything on the screen remains clearly visible. Thanks to the 100Hz refresh rate, you see smooth images. You can see who crosses the finish line first during an exciting race right away. Like to play games on a powerful PC? You can enjoy a 144Hz refresh rate.

Our expert review

Realistic images without reflections on the screen

  • A powerful contrast and rich colours
  • No reflections on the screen
  • Fast-paced action flows smoothly into view
  • No swivel base

The Samsung OLED S95D has a stylish slim screen with sharp images. Thanks to the OLED Glare Free layer, I still enjoy good image quality in my sun-drenched room without reflections on the screen. Vivid and colorful images I turn on a nature documentary to test the brightness and colors properly. I notice that the S95D shows the most colorful and bright images of all Samsung OLED televisions. The advantage of this OLED television is the Quantum Dots technology. All quantum dots each create their own color, giving the screen a larger color range. Thanks to the high brightness, I can easily distinguish the different shades of green from nature.

No reflections on the screen I think that the Samsung S95D has the best viewing angle quality of all Samsung televisions. Thanks to the OLED technology and the high brightness, the image can be seen well from every angle in the room. Thanks to the OLED Glare Free layer, light sources and reflections are not visible on the screen. I placed a bright lamp opposite the screen and indeed saw no reflections on the screen.

Impressive sound quality Thanks to the built-in soundbar and subwoofer, I enjoy a powerful and full sound. Thanks to the Object Tracking Sound+ sound technology, the sound moves with the movements on the screen. For example, you can follow the sound of cars speeding past during an exciting action film. Thanks to Dolby Atmos technology, the sound bounces off the ceiling to my viewing position. This means I can also hear sounds above me, such as an airplane flying over.

  • Doris

  • 30 August 2024

8,0/10 ()

Almost a shame to mount the foot

  • Image quality
  • Super thin
  • Matte screen

I was able to test this TV for a few weeks.

The Samsung TV is truly a picture to look at, both with the display on or off. Due to its very low thickness, the TV can be mounted almost flat against the wall. Thanks to the One-Connect box, you never have to be behind the screen to connect cables. The viewing angles of the screen are also very good, I could not discover any distortion of the colours. Despite all these reasons why the screen is perfect for hanging on the wall, Samsung still supplies a stand with it, so the TV can certainly also be used freestanding.

The image quality of the screen is very good, colours are bright and black is simply black as it should be with an OLED screen. However, where you have to watch out for reflections from windows or lamps in the house with most OLED TVs, Samsung has opted for a matte panel for this TV. This means that the TV can still be viewed well even in full sunlight.

I can definitely recommend the screen!

  • Stefan

  • 17 August 2024

  • Bright colors

Very nice TV with bright colors and sharp image. Matt screen so no reflection when the TV is off. Eight built-in speakers so a sound box is not necessary. Due to the one connect box there are no connections behind the TV, making the TV particularly thin and can be mounted tightly on the wall. In sight is only a wire to the one connect box. The image remains sharp when you look at the screen at 45 degrees.
